      "Cold blood products worsen hypothermia and coagulopathy. Always use a rapid infuser/fluid warmer for massive transfusion. Target patient temperature ≥36°C.",
      "Citrate toxicity from massive transfusion can cause hypocalcemia, leading to cardiac dysfunction and worsened coagulopathy. Monitor ionized calcium and replace with calcium gluconate or calcium chloride.",
      "Each unit of PRBC raises hemoglobin by approximately 1 g/dL. Each unit of platelets raises the count by approximately 30,000-50,000/μL.",
      "Fibrinogen is the first clotting factor to reach critically low levels during hemorrhage. Target fibrinogen >1.5-2.0 g/L. Cryoprecipitate or fibrinogen concentrate is given for levels <1.5 g/L.",
      "In trauma, the primary survey (ABCDE) and hemorrhage control take priority over diagnostic imaging. Direct pressure, tourniquets, and pelvic binders save lives.",
